      "title": "Happy who the riddle reads",
      "artist": "Michael A Ricciardi",
      "year": "2023",
      "description": "The song ('Happy Who The Riddle Read') was originally written/composed in the late 1980s (lyrics written in a notebook, song melody improvised and memorized; the 'bridge' section was improvised more recently) and borrows a short passage (the last verse of the three) from The Emerald Tablet (La Tabula Smaragdina, or Lawh al-Zumurudh) and should be well known to Hermeticists. The video was composed using found or appropriated imagery (film clips via archive.org, with some web-based public domain GIFs) and reflects a free-associative assemblage process.",
