      "id": "w_94714fafea59e8_19db024b230",
      "title": "Lux Vera 6023",
      "artist": "Samuele Scodeggio",
      "year": "2024",
      "description": "Freemasonry is one of the world's most secretive organizations, and for the first time, this documentary unveils long-hidden truths.\nPresenter Morris gains access to a stunning Masonic lodge in Brindisi, a city with deep Templar roots, considered ancestors of Freemasonry.\nThe film reveals unseen footage of the lodge, rituals, and explanations of Masonic symbols and artifacts. It also tackles sensitive topics through interviews with Freemasons of varying ranks, from initiates to Honorary Grand Master Stefano Erario.\nThis documentary offers a unique glimpse into a secretive world, revealing surprising answers and intertwining Freemasonry with modern life.",
